atest activity on your site, including the URL and title of the page that was accessed, the user name (if available) and the IP address of the viewer.','','none'),(3787,NULL,'default','<a href=\"@top-referrers\">Top referrers</a> displays where visitors came from (referrer URL).','','none'),(3788,NULL,'default','<a href=\"@top-pages\">Top pages</a> displays a list of pages ordered by how often they were viewed.','','none'),(3789,NULL,'default','<a href=\"@top-visitors\">Top visitors</a> shows you the most active visitors for your site and allows you to ban abusive visitors.','','none'),(3790,NULL,'default','Displaying popular content','','none'),(3791,NULL,'default','The module includes a <em>Popular content</em> block that displays the most viewed pages today and for all time, and the last content viewed. To use the block, enable <em>Count content views</em> on the <a href=\"@statistics-settings\">statistics settings page</a>, and then you can enable and configure the block on the <a href=\"@blocks\">blocks administration page</a>.','','none'),(3792,NULL,'default','Page view counter','','none'),(3793,NULL,'default','The Statistics module includes a counter for each page that increases whenever the page is viewed. To use the counter, enable <em>Count content views</em> on the <a href=\"@statistics-settings\">statistics settings page</a>, and set the necessary <a href=\"@permissions\">permissions</a> (<em>View content hits</em>) so that the counter is visible to the users.','','none'),(3794,NULL,'default','Administer statistics','','none'),(3795,NULL,'default','View content access statistics','','none'),(3796,NULL,'default','View content hits','','none'),(3797,NULL,'default','Control details about what and how your site logs access statistics.','','none'),(3798,NULL,'default','The Syslog module logs events by sending messages to the logging facility of your web server\'s operating system. Syslog is an operating system administrative logging tool that provides valuable information for use in system management and security auditing. Most suited to medium and large sites, Syslog provides filtering tools that allow messages to be routed by type and severity. For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\'@syslog\'>Syslog module</a> and PHP\'s <a href=\'@php_openlog\'>openlog</a> and <a href=\'@php_syslog\'>syslog</a> functions.','','none'),(3799,NULL,'default','Logging for UNIX, Linux, and Mac OS X','','none'),(3800,NULL,'default','On UNIX, Linux, and Mac OS X, the file <em>/etc/syslog.conf</em> defines the routing configuration. Messages can be flagged with the codes <code>LOG_LOCAL0</code> through <code>LOG_LOCAL7</code>. For information on Syslog facilities, severity levels, and how to set up <em>syslog.conf</em>, see the <em>syslog.conf</em> manual page on your command line.','','none'),(3801,NULL,'default','Logging for Microsoft Windows','','none'),(3802,NULL,'default','On Microsoft Windows, messages are always sent to the Event Log using the code <code>LOG_USER</code>.','','none'),(3803,NULL,'default','Syslog facility','','none'),(3804,NULL,'default','Depending on the system configuration, Syslog and other logging tools use this code to identify or filter messages from within the entire system log.','','none'),(3805,NULL,'default','The image %file could not be rotated because the imagerotate() function is not available in this PHP installation.','','none'),(3806,NULL,'default','The image %file could not be desaturated because the imagefilter() function is not available in this PHP installation.','','none'),(3807,NULL,'default','Screenshot for !theme theme','','none'),(3808,NULL,'default','Settings for !theme theme','','none'),(3809,NULL,'default','Disable !theme theme','','none'),(3810,NULL,'default','Set !theme as default theme','','none'),(3811,NULL,'default','Enable !theme theme','','none'),(3812,NULL,'default','Enable and set default','','none'),(3813,NULL,'default','Enable !theme as default theme','','